# Navigating with router links

With every link we click a new request is sent to the server and it returns a new page.

There is a special decorative that angular gives us. 

n Angular, RouterLink is a directive for navigating to a different route declaratively. Router.navigate and Router.navigateByURL are two methods available to the Router class to navigate imperatively in your component classes.

However, a single page application (SPA) does not have different pages to link to. Instead, it has different views to display to the user. To allow a user to navigate and change the view, you will want to use the RouterLink directive instead of href:

